{"cursor":"20955","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{ Horseraces infobox |class = Grade I |horse race = Santa Anita Derby |image =\n|caption = |location = Santa Anita Park Arcadia, California, USA |inaugurated\n= 1935 |race type = Thoroughbred - Flat racing |website =\n[http://www.santaanita.com/ Santa Anita Park] |distance = 1â miles (9 furlongs)\n|track = Dirt, Left-handed |qualification = Three-year-olds |weight = 122 lbs\n(55.3 kg) |purse = $1 million [http://www.drf.com/news/santa-anita-derby-purse-boosted-1-\nmillion \"Santa Anita Derby purse boosted to $1 million\"], [[Daily Racing Form]],\nNovember 16, 2010. |bonuses = }} The 'Santa Anita Derby' is an American\nGrade 1 thoroughbred horse race for three-year-olds run each April at Santa\nAnita Park in Arcadia, California and carries a purse of $1 million. Inaugurated\nin 1935, it is considered the most important West Coast stepping-stone to the\nKentucky Derby. Since its inception, seven Santa Anita Derby winners have gone\non to win the Kentucky Derby.\n\nNow run at a distance of 1 miles (9 Furlongs), for the first three years it was\n1 miles, and at 1 miles in 1947. Until 2008 the race had been run on dirt\nsurface. The race has been contested on Cushion Track (2008) and Pro-Ride (2009\n& 2010) artificial surfaces. In 2011, the race returned to dirt.\n\nPrep races to the Santa Anita Derby include the San Rafael Stakes, San Miguel\nStakes, San Felipe Stakes, Sham Stakes, San Vicente Stakes and the Santa\nCatalina Stakes, all run at Santa Anita Park.\n\nAs a result of World War II, there were no races held from 1942 to 1944.\n","linknr":414,"url":"Santa_Anita_Derby","recorded":1362665009,"links":12,"instances":["horseman","horse","horse","horse","horse","horse","jockey","horseman","mass","horse","horse","horse","horse","horse","horse","horse","horse","jockey"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Horse races in the United States","Horse races in California","Santa Anita Park","Flat horse races for thre